	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=365862><span id= >justifier</span></a><br><span id=notbold>4 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>ok first you do NOT need to do the messenger quest. all you need to do is sit in the seaferers roost in efp. when the drunk ,tykar, spawns just give him 4 droms champagnes. he will give you a blanket. then either have a friend make you a bog juice (brewing triv 21 = 1 water flask, 1 snake scale, 1 bottle) and an edible goo (baking triv 21 = 1 rat ear, 1 fire beetle eye). go to the prison under the arena in wfp and look in the cells til you find &quot;a prisoner&quot;. give him the blanket, bog juice, and edible goo. he will give you the key for his box in high keep. then go to hk and give the key to the assistant. *note* the banker will no longer accept items given so you will have to use the assistant. she will give you the letter for brother hayle. it has been said that you have to have ally faction. i have not attempted turn in yet but i am at warmly. it only took about 3hrs killing bandits and 55 sashes. i also made about 250pp for my efforts. not bad considering it had to be done anyhow. next just do the killing and loot hilt and testimony for turn in for sword. go to split paw and hand in first note. once he gives it back with instructions then hand in all items and viola, your very own fire breathing sword. good luck to all and hope this will help ease it a little.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
