	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=174358><span id= >bbronov</span></a><br><span id=notbold>2 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>my 2pp worth...another way to up your faction with Brother Hayle is to go a Bandit killing spree in WK. Collect the sashes and hand them into the Pally GM in Qeynos. Not only do you build faction with a number of folks, but the guy give you a weapon (bronze) or shield and a few pp for your trouble. Sell them to the vendor standing next to him. A good barometer of your faction is Brother Estle, found near the QH zone line in WK, of slightly further north in the little group of houses. He shares the same faction as Hayle, so you don't have to schlep into the Paw to find out your faction.<br><br>Sabathius Deovictus<br>48 Paladin, Kayne Bayle<br></p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
