	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=434&mid=107412280997038>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=434&mid=107412280997038>...</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=434&mid=107412280997038#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Jan 14th 6:28 PM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=143249><span id= >Talbot</span></a><br><span id=notbold>3 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I spent about an hour killing PH in Mistmoore to spawn, Xitcotl, a Troll SK.&nbsp;&nbsp;I had good luck getting him to pop only after an hour of camping.  When he popped, Jaccie, my fiancee, a 45 Cleric, came to my aid as quick as she could on horseback.  I had a pretty good tactic of pulling Xitcotl from deep inside MM to the zoneline.  We had several adds, both green and dark blue, during the fight.  Jaccie did a wonderful job of keeping up with heals, and I soon had a piece of my epic complete.  <br> <br>Now on to bigger things...  An hour later we headed to Freeport West to take on Sir Lucan D'lere, the Warrior Guildmaster of Freeport.  He is a corrupt invidual, as much as WFP is.  He lied to and decieved much of the good Clerics and Paladins in the Temple of Life.  He is level 48.    <br><br>We buffed up and I had Jaccie wait on the zone line to Eastern Commonlands.  If I was going to pull Sir Lucan the Warrior Guildmaster, A LOT of guards were obviously going to aggro.  I lulled as many guards as I could, but once I stunned Sir Lucan for the pull, he did a zonewide shout for a call to arms from his guards.  Seemingly every guard was on my tail and off I ran to Jaccie near the East Commonlands zone line.  I pulled the guards as close as I could to the zoneline before I finally zoned of aggro.  I had Jaccie chain Hail Sir Lucan to keep him at the zoneline while the other guards walked back to their posts.   As soon as I zoned back in, the beatdown commenced.  <br> <br>It was probably one of the longest fights I've ever done in EQ, including Agnarr the Stormlord in BoT to save Karana and fighting the War God, Rallos Zek.  Sir Lucan was commonly quading for 119 a pop, he resisted 70% of my stuns.  Jaccie did a wonderful job of casting Complete Heal as soon as I got down to under 20% health, very efficient.  Jaccie got down to 5% mana by the time things were said and done, and I still had my Lay of Hands ready to go.  It was  VERY, VERY close fight.  I can't stress that enough.  I honestly don't think we could of done it if were even one level lowers than we both were.  Jaccie had a KEI and I had a temp, and that helped tremendously!  <br> <br>Next, I had to do some tradeskill work and talk to some NPCs to get a few more items for the sword.  I also had to kill two other piddily mobs before I could do the final hand in.  I was distraught to find out that I did not have the necessary faction to complete the quest.  So I had to do 2 hours worth of faction work (handing 2gp at a time to Novashine in Qeynos), which was mind numbingly dull.  However, I made it, and was the proud new owner of a flaming sword of doom, the SoulFire.  <br><br>The sword itself sucks compared to other droppable 2HS out there, but it is more of a novelty item purely for the looks for Paladins.  It DOES have a REALLY useful effect of five charges of Complete Heal which will come in handy when we go on to take tough mobs.  I know it will be a life and a raid saver.  Thanks for reading!<br><br>Garritt - 44 Paladin of Stromm</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
